(23, 'BSEE', 'Bachelor of Science in Electrical Engineering', 'UGRD', 'CEAT', 'This curricular program offers an excellent opportunity for the students to acquire solid academic preparations in electrical and electronic circuit theory and analysis. Graduates of the program are expected to be fully equipped and able to enhance the level of their competencies as they chart their professional careers in the development mainstreams, particularly in power, electronic and computer engineering including equipment/instrument design. This curricular program was conceived in response to the dire need for well-trained electrical and electronic engineers in all sectors of development, both the local and global scales. In the Philippines, graduates of electrical engineering are key players as the country modernizes in agriculture systems and accelerates in rural-urban and industrial base for the 21st century. Each student can specialize in one or more of the following fields: (a) power engineering, (b) electronic engineering and (c) computer engineering. Moreover, the student may choose thesis research or practicum as a specialization course.', 1, NULL, NULL, 21, 'YES', NULL),
(18, 'BSABME', 'Bachelor of Science in Agribusiness Management and Entrepreneuship', 'UGRD', 'CEM', 'The Bachelor of Science in Agribusiness Management and Entrepreneurship (BSABME) program was born out of the need to strengthen the business side of agriculture. The basic idea was to blend knowledge of scientific agriculture with business management skills. Through the years, agribusiness as a concept and a field of study has evolved from solely the business side of agriculture to the management of the agribusiness companies’ network of supply chains. The growing importance of agribusiness to the Philippine economy has fueled the agribusiness sector’s growth and has spurred the demand for trained manpower to manage agribusiness companies. The BSABME program offers a combination of technical/agricultural courses and management/ business/ entrepreneurship courses. These are in addition to the prescribed GE courses which provide students with opportunities for lifelong learning in different aspects of life. The offering of such courses prepares BSABME students for managing agribusiness enterprises and institutions which provide agribusiness services.', 1, NULL, '2024-09-30 11:17:56', 18, 'YES', NULL),
(19, 'BSECO', 'Bachelor of Science in Economics', 'UGRD', 'CEM', 'The Bachelor of Science in Economics program was instituted in 1986. The program was born out of the necessity of constructing alternative development strategies for overcoming the economic crisis which beset the country during the period. These strategies required the consideration of prevailing economic concerns which included, among others, the heavy debt burden, poverty, unemployment and underemployment, unproductive and inefficient industries, as well as malnutrition. Furthermore, there was a need to better understand natural resource exploitation and its link to the country’s development. The BS Economics program aims to produce graduates who possess: 1) the necessary skills in quantitative and policy analyses for teaching and research in economics, 2)the ability to analyze, synthesize, and evaluate economic concepts, issues, and data relevant to policy decision-making in the public or private sectors, and 3) a deep appreciation of the economic issues and problems besetting College of Economics and Management 119 the country, as well as an objective and critical attitude towards the arguments and policies meant to address them.The BS Economics Program has two fields of specialization: Development Economics and Environmental Economics.', 1, NULL, NULL, 18, 'YES', NULL),
(1, 'BSA', 'Bachelor of Science in Agriculture', 'UGRD', 'CAFS', 'This program aims to educate students towards a career in scientifically based sustainable agriculture, to enable them to develop and effectively manage a self-reliant and economically viable agriculture-related enterprise, and to prepare them to become professionals with social commitment. Students may opt for a combination of thesis and practicum or major practice and special problem. The practicum and major practice options are farm/plant practice, research internship, agricultural entrepreneurship, teaching, and extension/community internship. This career can be pursued in any of the following major areas and fields of specialization.', 1, NULL, NULL, 21, 'YES', NULL),
(4, 'BACA', 'Bachelor of Arts in Communication Arts', 'UGRD', 'CAS', 'This program seeks to produce graduates who demonstrate proficiency in various theories of language, communication, literature, and performance, and exhibit analytical and integrative skills in the application of these theories in the cultural and creative industries and other settings. Students are trained to synthesize various humanistic worldviews through oral, written, and performative communication, as well as produce researches and creative works that promote the empowerment of the self and the nation.', 1, NULL, NULL, 18, 'YES', NULL),
