(172, 'AScF', 'Associate of Science in Forestry', 'ASSO', 'CFNR', 'The AScF program is a post-secondary/pre-baccalaureate program intended to support and enhance the interests of students in environment, forest and natural resources initially introduced during SHS. The program is designed both to be a terminal program and a ladderized program allowing students to either pursue employment or pursue higher learning (BS Forestry) after graduation. The curriculum incorporates general education and core technical forestry courses that provide basic technical know-how expected of forestry technicians. If qualified, students may apply to the BSF program that will provide them with a general and holistic knowledge and skills in forestry and forest resources management. The primary goal of both pathways (employment and higher learning) is to produce competent forest technicians/foresters and foster creative solutions to contribute to sustainable forest resources for the country and the world.', 1, NULL, NULL, 20, 'YES', NULL),
